column5: Well hopefully the rain holds of on the Kawartha lakes !!! Just wondering who's going fishing ??? In heading out shortly I guess ....
I'll be out on g bay
Looks like I slept in.LOL  Coffee and toast,and I,m off as well.
Good luck out there guys,I guess there will be a few reports later today  Maureen
I've been waiting in the garage for my guy to show up.... After 45 minutes I come inside to check OFC.... PM said "sorry, something came up" Anybody else want to go fishing? Grrrrr!
I'm leaving shortly for LPB.  That sucks Brian
Iam standing here looking at the boat but i don't know ......whats the wind & rain say .
Weather network says no rain and winds west up to  25 km/h by mid day Skip  Michael
looks to me like the bigger anchor will be  needed
Or stay on the west side of a smaller lake about 45 minutes away  Michael
Dang Brian that sux. I'm on shore today father son day 2 well he has a buddy coming over. I hope to get out in the afternoon good luck to everyone out there today
Good luck everyone!!!  I'm off to the bushes

How did you guys make out? Caught a few nice lm, biggest being a tad over three. Small mouth were all dinks. A few pike, biggest 32". Dad kept two of the smaller ones to eat. Was pretty rough out. First time I fully drained my two group 31s on my terrova.
